rrect.\nTrial 44: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'FISH', 'was', 'CAUGHT', 'by the', 'GIRL', 'on the', 'BOAT', 'on a', 'FRIDAY']. The comprehension probe is 'The fish was caught by the boy?'. You press <<n>> after <<1156>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 45: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'COUNT', 'that', 'KNEW', 'the', 'QUEEN', 'owned a', 'CASTLE', 'by the', 'LAKE']. The comprehension probe is 'The count knew the queen?'. You press <<y>> after <<2009>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 46: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'BOX', 'was', 'MADE', 'from', 'WOOD', 'and was', 'FULL', 'of', 'THINGS', 'that', 'SHINED']. The comprehension probe is 'The box was shiny?'. You press <<n>> after <<1590>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 47: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'thug', 'THAT', 'saw', 'THE', 'man', 'HAD A', 'hat', 'ON HIS', 'head']. The comprehension probe is 'The thug had a hat on his head?'. You press <<y>> after <<1273>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 48: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'cat', 'that the', 'DOG', 'fought', 'licked', 'ITS', 'wounds', 'in', 'THE', 'corner']. The comprehension probe is 'The cat fought the dog?'. You press <<n>> after <<3178>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 49: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'BOY', 'that the', 'girl', 'HELPED', 'got', 'an', 'A', 'on', 'the', 'TEST']. The comprehension probe is 'The boy got an A?'. You press <<y>> after <<1140>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 50: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'GUEST', 'that', 'KISSED', 'the', 'HOST', 'brought a', 'CAKE', 'to the', 'PARTY']. The comprehension probe is 'The guest brought a cake?'. You press <<d>> after <<1722>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 51: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'COOK', 'that the', 'maid', 'HUGGED', 'had', 'a', 'TEAR', 'on', 'her', 'CHEEK']. The comprehension probe is 'The cook hugged the maid?'. You press <<n>> after <<1774>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 52: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'CLERK', 'that the', 'boss', 'LIKED', 'had', 'a', 'DESK', 'by', 'the', 'WINDOW']. The comprehension probe is 'The clerk liked the boss?'. You press <<n>> af