{"text":"Welcome to the experiment. Thank you for participating! In each trial, you will read a sentence one word at a time, presented on the screen at a steady rhythm. When words appear in all capital letters, imagine reading this word with extra rhythmic emphasis. These will occur at a regular pattern like a rhythm. After reading the sentence, the experiment then tests your understanding of this sentence by asking you a question. You respond to this question with either 'yes' or 'no', indicating your response with the 'y' and 'n' keys respectively. If you have no idea of the answer, either because you found the sentence hard, or your concentration lapsed. Don't worry. Press 'd' for \"don't know\". This is totally fine, it is natural for your concentration to go up and down during an experiment like this and it's important you don't just randomly guess an answer. For example, if the sentence was \"The boy that the girl liked is wearing a hat\" and the question was \"the girl is wearing a hat\", the correct response would be 'n'. When the question appears on the screen, you are to respond as quickly as you can. If you take longer than 5 seconds, you will be reminded to speed up on the next trial. Accuracy is still important, however, so do not go too quickly. And unlike reading this sentence, during the trial, the sentence will flash up on the screen one or two words at a time, synchronised to an auditory tone. You control when each trial starts, so feel free to take short breaks to keep your concentration high. And you are always welcome to ask the experimenter questions during these breaks if anything is unclear. It is very important that you feel confident in your understanding of the task and are giving it your full attention. Making mistakes is part of the experiment, though, so do not worry when this happens. Good science is made possible by good participants, so thank you in advance for your cooperation—we really appreciate it! During the trials, keep your index fingers resting on the 'y' and 'n' key ready to press the button. Press space to start the main experiment.\nTrial 1: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'DOG', 'that', 'BARKED', 'is very', 'BIG', 'and very', 'FRIENDLY', 'but', 'DOESN’T', 'like', 'CATS']. The comprehension probe is 'The dog is very big?'. You press <<y>> after <<1523>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 2: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'bum', 'that the', 'COP', 'scared', 'crossed', 'THE', 'street', 'at', 'THE', 'light']. The comprehension probe is 'The bum crossed the street?'. You press <<y>> after <<1274>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 3: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'king', 'THAT', 'pleased', 'THE', 'guest', 'POURED THE', 'wine', 'FROM THE', 'jug']. The comprehension probe is 'The king pleased the guest?'. You press <<y>> after <<1390>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 4: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'cook', 'that the', 'MAID', 'hugged', 'had', 'A', 'tear', 'on', 'HER', 'cheek']. The comprehension probe is 'The cook hugged the maid?'. You press <<n>> after <<2958>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 5: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'dad', 'THAT', 'knew', 'THE', 'chef', 'HAD A', 'son', 'WITH A', 'limp']. The comprehension probe is 'The chef had a son?'. You press <<n>> after <<4080>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 6: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'shelf', 'that the', 'PIANO', 'bumped', 'had', 'SOME', 'dust', 'on', 'ITS', 'top']. The comprehension probe is 'The piano had dust on its top?'. You press <<n>> after <<2477>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 7: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'MAN', 'who was', 'SHORT', 'gave his', 'WIFE', 'some red', 'CANDLES', 'for her', 'BIRTHDAY']. The comprehension probe is 'The man was tall?'. You press <<n>> after <<1674>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 8: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'whale', 'THAT', 'bit', 'THE', 'shark', 'WON THE', 'fight', 'IN THE', 'end']. The comprehension probe is 'The whale won the fight?'. You press <<y>> after <<2727>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 9: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'guest', 'that the', 'HOST', 'kissed', 'brought', 'A', 'cake', 'to', 'THE', 'party']. The comprehension probe is 'The guest brought a cake?'. You press <<y>> after <<3378>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 10: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'APPLES', 'that', 'THE', 'couple', 'BOUGHT', 'at the', 'MARKET', 'were', 'RED']. The comprehension probe is 'The couple bought some apples?'. You press <<y>> after <<2358>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 11: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'tradie', 'THAT', 'thanked', 'THE', 'man', 'LEFT HIS', 'wallet', 'IN THE', 'car']. The comprehension probe is 'The man thanked the tradie?'. You press <<n>> after <<1841>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 12: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'TRUCK', 'that', 'BUMPED', 'the', 'CAR', 'had a', 'MAN', 'at the', 'WHEEL']. The comprehension probe is 'The truck had a man at the wheel?'. You press <<y>> after <<3209>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 13: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'CONCERT', 'started', 'LATER', 'than', 'WHAT', 'the', 'LADY', 'told the', 'TRAVELER']. The comprehension probe is 'The concert started early?'. You press <<n>> after <<2142>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 14: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'hat', 'THAT', 'matched', 'THE', 'skirt', 'HAD A', 'bow', 'IN THE', 'back']. The comprehension probe is 'The hat had a bow?'. You press <<y>> after <<3998>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 15: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'DEAN', 'that the', 'guard', 'HEARD', 'made', 'a', 'CALL', 'about', 'the', 'MATTER']. The comprehension probe is 'The dean heard the guard?'. You press <<n>> after <<2711>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 16: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'MAN', 'was very', 'HUNGRY', 'after the', 'MEETING', 'so', 'HAD', 'lunch', 'EARLY']. The comprehension probe is 'The man was hungry?'. You press <<y>> after <<1774>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 17: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'thief', 'that the', 'GUARD', 'saw', 'had', 'A', 'gun', 'in', 'HIS', 'holster']. The comprehension probe is 'The guard saw the thief?'. You press <<y>> after <<2492>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 18: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'BOOK