You press <<y>> after <<2106>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 62: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'CAR', 'that was', 'NEW', 'had', 'JUST', 'been', 'CLEANED', 'by', 'THE', 'old', 'LADY']. The comprehension probe is 'The car was new?'. You press <<y>> after <<1207>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 63: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'RING', 'that', 'WAS', 'sadly', 'LOST', 'was', 'FOUND', 'by the', 'FAT', 'and', 'VERY', 'happy', 'PRIEST']. The comprehension probe is 'The priest was sad?'. You press <<n>> after <<838>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 64: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'MAN', 'that the', 'nurse', 'PHONED', 'left', 'his', 'PILLS', 'at', 'the', 'OFFICE']. The comprehension probe is 'The man phoned the nurse?'. You press <<n>> after <<1891>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 65: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'GROOM', 'that', 'CHARMED', 'the', 'AUNT', 'raised a', 'TOAST', 'to the', 'PARENTS']. The comprehension probe is 'The groom raised a toast?'. You press <<y>> after <<1574>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 66: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'MAN', 'who was', 'SHORT', 'gave his', 'WIFE', 'some red', 'CANDLES', 'for her', 'BIRTHDAY']. The comprehension probe is 'The man was short?'. You press <<y>> after <<1826>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 67: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'tradie', 'THAT', 'thanked', 'THE', 'man', 'LEFT HIS', 'wallet', 'IN THE', 'car']. The comprehension probe is 'The tradie thanked the man?'. You press <<y>> after <<756>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 68: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'BOOK', 'that the', 'LADY', 'with a', 'TATTOO', 'had', 'WRITTEN', 'was her', 'BEST', 'book', 'YET']. The comprehension probe is 'The lady wrote a book?'. You press <<y>> after <<588>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 69: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'KNIGHT', 'that', 'HELPED', 'the', 'KING', 'sent a', 'GIFT', 'from his', 'CASTLE']. The comprehension probe is 'The king helped the knight?'. You press <<n>> after <<1456>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 70: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'shelf', 'THAT', 'bumped', 'THE', 'piano', 'HAD SOME', 'dust', 'ON ITS', 'top']. The comprehension probe is 'The piano had dust on its top?'. You press <<n>> after <<1056>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 71: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'APPLES', 'that', 'THE', 'couple', 'BOUGHT', 'at the', 'MARKET', 'were', 'RED']. The comprehension probe is 'The couple bought green apples?'. You press <<n>> after <<1506>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 72: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'thief', 'THAT', 'saw', 'THE', 'guard', 'HAD A', 'gun', 'IN HIS', 'holster']. The comprehension probe is 'The thief had a gun?'. You press <<y>> after <<638>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 73: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'FRUIT', 'that the', 'cake', 'SQUASHED', 'made', 'a', 'MESS', 'in', 'the', 'BAG']. The comprehension probe is 'The fruit squashed the cake?'. You press <<y>> after <<2008>> ms. Incorrect.","experiment":"hilton2021_comprehension_exp1","participant_id":"013","age":26,"gender":"male","first_language":"English","handedness":"left","country_of_residence":"Australia"}
{"text":"Welcome to the experiment. Thank you for participating! In each trial, you will read a sentence one word at a time, presented on the screen at a steady rhythm. When words appear in all capital letters, imagine reading this word with extra rhythmic emphasis. These will occur at a regular pattern like a rhythm. After reading the sentence, the experiment then tests your understanding of this sentence by asking you a question. You respond to this question with either 'yes' or 'no', indicating your response with the 'y' and 'n' keys respectively. If you have no idea of the answer, either because you found the sentence hard, or your concentration lapsed. Don't worry. Press 'd' for \"don't know\". This is totally fine, it is natural for your concentration to go up and down during an experiment like this and it's important you don't just randomly guess an answer. For example, if the sentence was \"The boy that the girl liked is wearing a hat\" and the question was \"the girl is wearing a hat\", the correct response would be 'n'. When the question appears on the screen, you are to respond as quickly as you can. If you take longer than 5 seconds, you will be reminded to speed up on the next trial. Accuracy is still important, however, so do not go too quickly. And unlike reading this sentence, during the trial, the sentence will flash up on the screen one or two words at a time, synchronised to an auditory tone. You control when each trial starts, so feel free to take short breaks to keep your concentration high. And you are always welcome to ask the experimenter questions during these breaks if anything is unclear. It is very important that you feel confident in your understanding of the task and are giving it your full attention. Making mistakes is part of the experiment, though, so do not worry when this happens. Good science is made possible by good participants, so thank you in advance for your cooperation—we really appreciate it! During the trials, keep your index fingers resting on the 'y' and 'n' key ready to press the button. Press space to start the main experiment.\nTrial 1: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'COLOUR', 'of the', 'HOUSE', 'was', 'BRIGHTER', 'than the', 'MEN', 'who travelled', 'EXPECTED']. The comprehension probe is 'The men travelled?'. You press <<y>> after <<2935>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 2: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'GIRL', 'that', 'PUSHED', 'the', 'NERD', 'broke the', 'VASE', 'with the', 'FLOWERS']. The comprehension probe is 'The girl broke the vase?'. You press <<y>> after <<2839>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 3: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'PIANO', 'was well', 'PLAYED', 'by', 'THE', 'old', 'LADY', 'but', 'IT', 'was', 'NOT', 'in', 'TUNE']. The comprehension probe is 'The piano was well played?'. You press <<y>> after <<1355>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 4: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'dad', 'THAT', 'knew', 'THE', 'chef', 'HAD A', 'son', 'WITH A', 'limp']. The comprehension probe is 'The chef knew the dad?'. You press <<d>> after <<5642>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 5: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'KING', 'that', 'PLEASED', 'the', 'GUEST', 'poured the', 'WINE', 'from the', 'JUG']. The comprehension probe is 'The guest pleased the king?'. You press <<y>> after <<4857>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 6: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'fox', 'THAT', 'chased', 'THE', 'wolf', 'HURT ITS', 'paws', 'ON THE', 'way']. The comprehension probe is 'The fox chased the wolf?'. You press <<n>> after <<3152>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 7: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'SAILOR', 'that the', 'banker', 'PUSHED', 'hurt', 'his', 'FOOT', 'in', 'the', 'BRAWL']. The comprehension probe is 'The banker pushed the sailor?'. You press <<y>> after <<5541>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 8: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'PRINCE', 'that the', 'girl', 'HELPED', 'had', 'a', 'HEAD', 'of', 'blonde', 'HAIR']. The comprehension probe is 'The girl had blonde hair?'. You press <<y>> after <<1338>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 9: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'car', 'that the', 'TRUCK', 'pulled', 'had', 'A', 'scratch', 'on', 'THE', 'door']. The comprehension probe is 'The truck had a scratch?'. You press <<n>> after <<2970>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 10: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'DESSERT', 'was', 'SERVED', 'with', 'CUSTARD', 'and', 'FRUIT', 'then', 'THERE', 'was', 'COFFEE']. The comprehension probe is 'The coffee was after dessert?'. You press <<n>> after <<3174>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 11: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'CAT', 'chased the', 'BIRD', 'but', 'IT', 'flew', 'AWAY', 'into the', 'SUNSET']. The comprehension probe is 'The cat chased the bird?'. You press <<y>> after <<3891>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 12: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'priest', 'THAT', 'paid', 'THE', 'cook', 'SIGNED THE', 'check', 'AT THE', 'bank']. The comprehension probe is 'The priest signed the check?'. You press <<y>> after <<1688>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 13: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'knight', 'THAT', 'helped', 'THE', 'king', 'SENT A', 'gift', 'FROM HIS', 'castle']. The comprehension probe is 'The king sent a gift?'. You press <<n>> after <<6710>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 14: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'shelf', 'that the', 'PIANO', 'bumped', 'had', 'SOME', 'dust', 'on', 'ITS', 'top']. The comprehension probe is 'The shelf had some dust on its top?'. You press <<n>> after <<2721>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 15: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'tradie', 'THAT', 'thanked', 'THE', 'man', 'LEFT HIS', 'wallet', 'IN THE', 'car']. The comprehension probe is 'The man thanked the tradie?'. You press <<d>> after <<12879>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 16: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'FRIEND', 'that the', 'bride', 'TEASED', 'told', 'a', 'JOKE', 'about', 'the', 'PAST']. The comprehension probe is 'The friend teased the bride?'. You press <<n>> after <<1705>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 17: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'GUEST', 'that the', 'host', 'KISSED', 'brought', 'a', 'CAKE', 'to', 'the', 'PARTY']. The comprehension probe is 'The host kissed the guest?'. You press <<y>> after