{"text":"Welcome to the experiment. Thank you for participating! In each trial, you will read a sentence one word at a time, presented on the screen at a steady rhythm. When words appear in all capital letters, imagine reading this word with extra rhythmic emphasis. These will occur at a regular pattern like a rhythm. After reading the sentence, the experiment then tests your understanding of this sentence by asking you a question. You respond to this question with either 'yes' or 'no', indicating your response with the 'y' and 'n' keys respectively. If you have no idea of the answer, either because you found the sentence hard, or your concentration lapsed. Don't worry. Press 'd' for \"don't know\". This is totally fine, it is natural for your concentration to go up and down during an experiment like this and it's important you don't just randomly guess an answer. For example, if the sentence was \"The boy that the girl liked is wearing a hat\" and the question was \"the girl is wearing a hat\", the correct response would be 'n'. When the question appears on the screen, you are to respond as quickly as you can. If you take longer than 5 seconds, you will be reminded to speed up on the next trial. Accuracy is still important, however, so do not go too quickly. And unlike reading this sentence, during the trial, the sentence will flash up on the screen one or two words at a time, synchronised to an auditory tone. You control when each trial starts, so feel free to take short breaks to keep your concentration high. And you are always welcome to ask the experimenter questions during these breaks if anything is unclear. It is very important that you feel confident in your understanding of the task and are giving it your full attention. Making mistakes is part of the experiment, though, so do not worry when this happens. Good science is made possible by good participants, so thank you in advance for your cooperation—we really appreciate it! During the trials, keep your index fingers resting on the 'y' and 'n' key ready to press the button. Press space to start the main experiment.\nTrial 1: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'GIRL', 'and the', 'BOY', 'that', 'OWNED', 'the', 'HORSE', 'had', 'MUD', 'on their', 'CLOTHES']. The comprehension probe is 'The horse was muddy?'. You press <<n>> after <<2159>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 2: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'fox', 'that the', 'WOLF', 'chased', 'hurt', 'ITS', 'paws', 'on', 'THE', 'way']. The comprehension probe is 'The wolf hurt its paws?'. You press <<y>> after <<2961>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 3: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'SAILOR', 'that the', 'banker', 'PUSHED', 'hurt', 'his', 'FOOT', 'in', 'the', 'BRAWL']. The comprehension probe is 'The sailor pushed the banker?'. You press <<n>> after <<2293>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 4: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'man', 'THAT', 'phoned', 'THE', 'nurse', 'LEFT HIS', 'pills', 'AT THE', 'office']. The comprehension probe is 'The nurse left the pills?'. You press <<n>> after <<1807>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 5: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'GIRL', 'on', 'THE', 'school', 'TRIP', 'saw a', 'FROG', 'and', 'LATER', 'she', 'SAW', 'a', 'MOUSE']. The comprehension probe is 'The girl saw a frog?'. You press <<y>> after <<1541>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 6: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'FRIEND', 'that the', 'bride', 'TEASED', 'told', 'a', 'JOKE', 'about', 'the', 'PAST']. The comprehension probe is 'The bride teased the friend?'. You press <<n>> after <<3228>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 7: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'BOAT', 'that', 'CHASED', 'the', 'YACHT', 'made a', 'TURN', 'at the', 'BOATHOUSE']. The comprehension probe is 'The boat made a turn?'. You press <<y>> after <<3179>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 8: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'MAN', 'was very', 'HUNGRY', 'after the', 'MEETING', 'so', 'HAD', 'lunch', 'EARLY']. The comprehension probe is 'The man was hungry?'. You press <<y>> after <<1892>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 9: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'cat', 'that the', 'DOG', 'fought', 'licked', 'ITS', 'wounds', 'in', 'THE', 'corner']. The comprehension probe is 'The dog fought the cat?'. You press <<y>> after <<3964>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 10: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'PRIEST', 'that the', 'nun', 'THANKED', 'left', 'the', 'CHURCH', 'in', 'a', 'HURRY']. The comprehension probe is 'The priest left the church?'. You press <<y>> after <<3646>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 11: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'GROOM', 'that', 'CHARMED', 'the', 'AUNT', 'raised a', 'TOAST', 'to the', 'PARENTS']. The comprehension probe is 'The aunt raised a toast?'. You press <<n>> after <<1555>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 12: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'boss', 'THAT', 'mocked', 'THE', 'clerk', 'HAD A', 'crush', 'ON THE', 'intern']. The comprehension probe is 'The clerk mocked the boss?'. You press <<n>> after <<3329>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 13: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'HAT', 'that', 'MATCHED', 'the', 'SKIRT', 'had a', 'BOW', 'in the', 'BACK']. The comprehension probe is 'The skirt matched the hat?'. You press <<y>> after <<3614>> ms. Incorrect.\nTrial 14: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'WHALE', 'that the', 'shark', 'BIT', 'won', 'the', 'FIGHT', 'in', 'the', 'END']. The comprehension probe is 'The shark won the fight?'. You press <<n>> after <<3012>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 15: The sentence stimuli is ['The', 'BOX', 'was', 'MADE', 'from', 'WOOD', 'and was', 'FULL', 'of', 'THINGS', 'that', 'SHINED']. The comprehension probe is 'The box was full of things?'. You press <<y>> after <<3462>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 16: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'cop', 'that the', 'SPY', 'met', 'wrote', 'A', 'book', 'about', 'THE', 'case']. The comprehension probe is 'The spy wrote a book?'. You press <<n>> after <<3112>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 17: The sentence stimuli is ['THE', 'dancer', 'that the', 'GUY', 'liked', 'was', 'A', 'chef', 'in', 'THE', 'city']. The comprehension probe is 'The guy liked the dancer?'. You press <<y>> after <<5050>> ms. Correct.\nTrial 18: The senten